text: The Technische Universität München (TUM; University of Technology, Munich; Technical University of Munich) is a research university with campuses in Munich, Garching and Freising-Weihenstephan. It was founded in 1868. The university alumni and professor list include 17 Nobel Prize winners. As of winter semester 2018 TUM has 41.375 students, 566 professors, and 10.501 staff members. ==References== Category:1868 establishments in Europe Category:Buildings and structures in Munich Munich Munich Category:Organizations based in Munich Category:1860s establishments in Germany
